# RTK — Mandatory Shell Prefix

Every shell command MUST be prefixed with `rtk`.

```
❌ git status / dotnet build / npm test
✅ rtk git status / rtk dotnet build / rtk npm test
```

PowerShell chains — prefix **each** segment:

```powershell
rtk git add . ; rtk git commit -m "msg"
```

Visibility: before each Shell tool call show:

`RTK ▸ rtk <exact command>`

If RTK has no filter, it passes through — still prefix.

Exception: active debugging of verbose output (`rtk proxy <cmd>` preferred).
